Coloration: extremely variable, mainly testaceous, reddish and black (see 
Fig. 1−3
).

Male: Abdominal terga sclerotised for most part, outer areas of each segment broadly pale. Internal apodeme on anterior margin of sternum VII broad and blunt and extending to about 1/3 length of sternum VI. Pygophore (
Fig. 7
) foramen in dorsal view with a conspicuous notch at about mid length. Paramere (
Fig. 8
) with dorsal flange more prominent than ventral lobe, blade broadly pointed, sickle-shaped. Aedeagus (
Fig. 9
) with phallotheca moderately pigmented in a broad band, conjunctiva tubular, membranous, gradually narrowed towards upper end, body and wings of ejaculatory reservoir (
Fig. 10
) fused and reduced, vesica with large sclerotised lobe, lobes basal to this lobe indistinct, ejaculatory duct inside vesica with 6–7 turns, secondary gonopore slightly flaring.

Female: Abdominal terga sclerotised in the form of a broad band along midline, outer areas of each tergite broadly pale, pale areas broader than in male. Spermatheca (
Fig. 11
) saccoid, bulb almost spherical, slightly wider than duct which has 1 coil and 2–3 twists, basal part narrow. Ovipositor with first ramus traversing to almost entire length of first gonapophysis; second gonapophysis blade-like.
